Coram Rege (No. 359) Easter 24 Ed. III. m. 3d.

[The commencement is in practically the same language.]

Et modo coram domino Rege veniunt predicti Prior et Fratres per Robertum de Acastre attornatum suum, et predictus Radulfus quarto die placiti solempnitur vocatus non venit, et vicecomes retornavit quod scire fecit ei per Johannem de Kirkeby et Johannem de Pykeryng 3 Et super hoc iidem Prior et Fratres petunt execucionem etc. Ideo consideratum est quod iidem Prior et Fratres recuperent seisinam suam versus eum de predicto manerio curn pertinenciis, et idem Radulfus sine die ete. by Sir Ralph, and before the suppression of their Order belonged to the Templars. Last Trinity Term the action was adjourned because Sir Ralph was then beyond the seas in the King's service, and had a writ os protection from the 4th of June up to Michaelmas.

The Sheriff returned that there had been no time to serve process, and he was directed to serve process by the octave of Mardnmas, on which day the Prior attended but the Sheriff had not sent the writ.
